### [Romans Chapter 11](../../../bib/kjv/rom011.htm#001.md)

[Romans 11:1](../../../bib/kjv/rom011.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">rom 11:1</span></span>

SAME SUBJECT CONTINUED AND CONCLUDED--THE ULTIMATE INBRINGING OF ALL
ISRAEL, TO BE, WITH THE GENTILES, ONE KINGDOM OF GOD ON THE EARTH. (Rom.
11:1-36)

I say then, Hath--"Did"

God cast away his people? God forbid--Our Lord did indeed announce that
"the kingdom of God should be taken from Israel" ([Mat
21:41](../../../bib/kjv/mat021.htm#041).md); and when asked by the Eleven,
after His resurrection, if He would at that time "restore the kingdom to
Israel," His reply is a virtual admission that Israel was in some sense
already out of covenant ([Act 1:9](../../../bib/kjv/act001.htm#009).md).
Yet here the apostle teaches that, in two respects, Israel was not "cast
away"; First, Not totally; Second, Not finally. FIRST, Israel is not
wholly cast away.

