of the tribe of Benjamin-- ([Phi 3:5](../../../bib/kjv/phi003.htm#005).md),
that tribe which, on the revolt of the ten tribes, constituted, with
Judah, the one faithful kingdom of God ([Kg1
12:21](../../../bib/kjv/kg1012.htm#021).md), and after the captivity was,
along with Judah, the kernel of the Jewish nation ([Ezr
4:1](../../../bib/kjv/ezr004.htm#001.md); [Ezr
10:9](../../../bib/kjv/ezr010.htm#009).md).

