is just the converse of [Rom 11:21](../../../bib/kjv/rom011.htm#021.md) :
"As the excision of the merely engrafted Gentiles through unbelief is a
thing much more to be expected than was the excision of the natural
Israel, before it happened; so the restoration of Israel, when they
shall be brought to believe in Jesus, is a thing far more in the line of
what we should expect, than the admission of the Gentiles to a standing
which they never before enjoyed."

